// Template for local Debug signing. Copy to `Local.xcconfig` (gitignored)
// and replace with your own Developer ID, Apple Development identity, or
// keep ad-hoc by leaving the file absent.
//
// Why: ad-hoc signing ("-") rotates the binary's signature hash on every
// rebuild, which makes macOS treat each Debug build as a new app and
// re-prompts TCC permissions (Documents, Files-and-Folders, Screen
// Recording, etc.) on every relaunch. A stable signing identity makes
// TCC remember the grants across rebuilds.
//
// Find your identities with:
//   security find-identity -v -p codesigning
//
// Then fill in below (example uses Developer ID; "Apple Development" works
// too for personal Apple IDs without a paid Developer account).

CODE_SIGN_STYLE = Manual
CODE_SIGN_IDENTITY = Developer ID Application: Your Name (YOURTEAMID)
DEVELOPMENT_TEAM = YOURTEAMID
